# Git Workflow

## Commit Messages

- Use conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `test:`, `refactor:`, `chore:`
- Keep subject line under 72 characters
- Use imperative mood: "add lead endpoint" not "added lead endpoint"

## What to Commit

- Never commit `.env`, credentials, or secrets
- Never commit `__pycache__/`, `.pyc`, or IDE config
- Keep `uploads/` out of version control (add to `.gitignore`)
- Commit `requirements.txt` / `pyproject.toml` with pinned versions

## Branching

- `main` — stable, deployable code
- Feature branches: `feat/lead-crud`, `fix/email-validation`
